./library/prompts/triage/eval-corpus.jsonl:76:{"id":"corpus-4f627e852b5a","source_repo":"ddx","expected_class":"atomic","rationale":"closed with commit evidence and no decomposition signal","title":"Migrate bead execution and worker smoke specs to fixture data","description":"## Context\n\nThe frontend e2e specs for beads, executions, and workers require backend data and currently fail when Playwright serves static preview output without the Go DDx server. After the fixture-backed runner exists, these specs should use the seeded `.ddx/beads.jsonl`, docs library, and any execution/worker fixture state available from the runner instead of relying on developer-local DDx state.\n\nUpdate the backend-data smoke specs so they pass against the self-contained fixture while preserving coverage of bead lists/status, execution views, and worker-related UI/API behavior.\n\n## In-scope files\n\n- `cli/internal/server/frontend/e2e/beads-smoke.spec.ts`.\n- `cli/internal/server/frontend/e2e/executions.spec.ts`.\n- `cli/internal/server/frontend/e2e/workers.spec.ts`.\n\n## Out-of-scope\n\n- `cli/internal/server/frontend/e2e/app.spec.ts`.\n- `cli/internal/server/frontend/e2e/navigation.spec.ts` and `src/routes/layout.e2e.ts`.\n- `cli/internal/server/frontend/e2e/screenshots.spec.ts` and any visual baseline rework.\n- `cli/internal/server/frontend/playwright.config.ts` and fixture creation except reading the fixture IDs/data created by the prerequisite bead.\n- `cli/internal/server/frontend/e2e/demo-recording.spec.ts` and `playwright.demo.config.ts`.\n- Go server source changes under `cli/internal/server/`.\n- Test deletion, `.skip`, or broad assertion weakening.\n\n## Rollback / cleanup\n\nIf a spec needs additional fixture records, keep the fixture deterministic and self-contained. Do not point tests at the repository's live `.ddx/` tracker or developer-specific worker state.","acceptance":"cd cli/internal/server/frontend \u0026\u0026 bun run test:e2e e2e/beads-smoke.spec.ts e2e/executions.spec.ts e2e/workers.spec.ts\ncd cli/internal/server/frontend \u0026\u0026 git diff --exit-code -- playwright.demo.config.ts e2e/demo-recording.spec.ts","labels":["area:test","area:frontend","kind:test-infra","phase:test"],"bead":{"id":"ddx-d15b6aa1","title":"Migrate bead execution and worker smoke specs to fixture data","status":"closed","issue_type":"task","description":"## Context\n\nThe frontend e2e specs for beads, executions, and workers require backend data and currently fail when Playwright serves static preview output without the Go DDx server. After the fixture-backed runner exists, these specs should use the seeded `.ddx/beads.jsonl`, docs library, and any execution/worker fixture state available from the runner instead of relying on developer-local DDx state.\n\nUpdate the backend-data smoke specs so they pass against the self-contained fixture while preserving coverage of bead lists/status, execution views, and worker-related UI/API behavior.\n\n## In-scope files\n\n- `cli/internal/server/frontend/e2e/beads-smoke.spec.ts`.\n- `cli/internal/server/frontend/e2e/executions.spec.ts`.\n- `cli/internal/server/frontend/e2e/workers.spec.ts`.\n\n## Out-of-scope\n\n- `cli/internal/server/frontend/e2e/app.spec.ts`.\n- `cli/internal/server/frontend/e2e/navigation.spec.ts` and `src/routes/layout.e2e.ts`.\n- `cli/internal/server/frontend/e2e/screenshots.spec.ts` and any visual baseline rework.\n- `cli/internal/server/frontend/playwright.config.ts` and fixture creation except reading the fixture IDs/data created by the prerequisite bead.\n- `cli/internal/server/frontend/e2e/demo-recording.spec.ts` and `playwright.demo.config.ts`.\n- Go server source changes under `cli/internal/server/`.\n- Test deletion, `.skip`, or broad assertion weakening.\n\n## Rollback / cleanup\n\nIf a spec needs additional fixture records, keep the fixture deterministic and self-contained. Do not point tests at the repository's live `.ddx/` tracker or developer-specific worker state.","ac