nternal/agent/execute_bead_land.go and tests, or server worker landing wrapper if that is the correct ownership point\\n- config schema/types if a post-land check command must be introduced\\n\\nOut-of-scope:\\n- Implementing every project-specific build command\\n- Changing execute-bead post-run checks before land\\n- Remote force-push behavior; never force-push.","acceptance":"1. A regression test configures a failing post-land command and verifies the target branch is restored to its pre-land SHA.\\n2. The result is preserved under refs/ddx/iterations with a reason naming the failed post-land gate.\\n3. A passing command leaves the target branch advanced.\\n4. cd cli \u0026\u0026 go test ./internal/agent -run 'TestLand_.*PostLand' passes.","labels":["area:agent","area:land-coordinator","kind:safety","severity:critical"],"parent":"ddx-efe058be"}}
