./library/prompts/triage/eval-corpus.jsonl:126:{"id":"corpus-862310dae8d9","source_repo":"ddx","expected_class":"atomic","rationale":"closed with commit evidence and no decomposition signal","title":"integration: persist close provenance in the landed tracker commit","description":"Review finding from fresh-eyes review.\nFile: cli/cmd/bead.go:518\nCategory: integration\nSeverity: medium\nDescription: The new close flow writes bead status first, auto-commits .ddx/beads.jsonl, and only then writes closing_commit_sha back to the store. In a clean temp git repo with git.auto_commit=always and DDX_BEAD_DIR unset, running 'ddx bead close \u003cid\u003e' leaves 'git status --short' dirty with ' M .ddx/beads.jsonl'. The landed HEAD commit 9494afc82408cac9a650d616fc3207197e1dfbd6 contains only the status=open-\u003eclosed change, while the durable closing_commit_sha appears only in the uncommitted worktree diff. That means the command still fails to land close provenance atomically and leaves replay/audit metadata outside the recorded close commit.\nSuggested fix: Restructure bead close so the recorded closing_commit_sha is present in the same landed commit that closes the bead, or perform and persist a second deterministic commit/update so git status is clean after close and HEAD contains the final provenance-bearing row.","acceptance":"With git.auto_commit=always in a git repo and DDX_BEAD_DIR unset, running 'ddx bead close \u003cid\u003e' leaves 'git status --short' clean, and 'git show HEAD -- .ddx/beads.jsonl' includes the bead row with closing_commit_sha equal to 'git rev-parse HEAD' rather than requiring an extra uncommitted worktree update","labels":["helix","phase:build","review-finding","severity:medium"],"bead":{"id":"hx-73c95bab","title":"integration: persist close provenance in the landed tracker commit","status":"closed","issue_type":"task","description":"Review finding from fresh-eyes review.\nFile: cli/cmd/bead.go:518\nCategory: integration\nSeverity: medium\nDescription: The new close flow writes bead status first, auto-commits .ddx/beads.jsonl, and only then writes closing_commit_sha back to the store. In a clean temp git repo with git.auto_commit=always and DDX_BEAD_DIR unset, running 'ddx bead close \u003cid\u003e' leaves 'git status --short' dirty with ' M .ddx/beads.jsonl'. The landed HEAD commit 9494afc82408cac9a650d616fc3207197e1dfbd6 contains only the status=open-\u003eclosed change, while the durable closing_commit_sha appears only in the uncommitted worktree diff. That means the command still fails to land close provenance atomically and leaves replay/audit metadata outside the recorded close commit.\nSuggested fix: Restructure bead close so the recorded closing_commit_sha is present in the same landed commit that closes the bead, or perform and persist a second deterministic commit/update so git status is clean after close and HEAD contains the final provenance-bearing row.","acceptance":"With git.auto_commit=always in a git repo and DDX_BEAD_DIR unset, running 'ddx bead close \u003cid\u003e' leaves 'git status --short' clean, and 'git show HEAD -- .ddx/beads.jsonl' includes the bead row with closing_commit_sha equal to 'git rev-parse HEAD' rather than requiring an extra uncommitted worktree update","labels":["helix","phase:build","review-finding","severity:medium"],"parent":"hx-df089a3d"}}
