./library/prompts/triage/eval-corpus.jsonl:155:{"id":"corpus-abb17c03e9cc","source_repo":"ddx","expected_class":"atomic","rationale":"closed with commit evidence and no decomposition signal","title":"integration: closing_commit_sha points ddx-1210706d at a mixed commit","description":"Review finding from fresh-eyes review.\nFile: .ddx/beads.jsonl:1\nCategory: integration\nSeverity: medium\nDescription: Commit 9653820 rewrites ddx-1210706d.closing_commit_sha to e51936a9300b162ab655ffe6c1150d6ba5de06c4, but that target commit contains unrelated agent/runtime changes in cli/cmd/agent_execute_bead.go, cli/internal/agent/types.go, and tests in addition to the tracker-governance work. FEAT-019 uses closing_commit_sha as replay provenance and compares against that commit's diff, so this bead now points replay/evidence at a mixed implementation boundary rather than just the work governed by ddx-1210706d.\nSuggested fix: Record a closing_commit_sha only when the referenced commit isolates ddx-1210706d's governed tracker/concern changes, or clear the field for this backfilled bead so replay falls back to sessionless mode instead of using misleading provenance.","acceptance":"ddx bead show ddx-1210706d --json either omits closing_commit_sha or points to a commit where 'git show --name-only --format=oneline \u003cclosing_commit_sha\u003e' lists only files governed by ddx-1210706d (.ddx/beads.jsonl and docs/helix/01-frame/concerns.md)","labels":["helix","phase:build","review-finding"],"bead":{"id":"hx-7f1af6d1","title":"integration: closing_commit_sha points ddx-1210706d at a mixed commit","status":"closed","issue_type":"task","description":"Review finding from fresh-eyes review.\nFile: .ddx/beads.jsonl:1\nCategory: integration\nSeverity: medium\nDescription: Commit 9653820 rewrites ddx-1210706d.closing_commit_sha to e51936a9300b162ab655ffe6c1150d6ba5de06c4, but that target commit contains unrelated agent/runtime changes in cli/cmd/agent_execute_bead.go, cli/internal/agent/types